title: Rinkeby Faucet offline: context deadline exceeded
body:
Faucet offline again, @karalabe maybe restart?

![screen shot 2018-09-06 at 8 42 09 am](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18633790/45158034-cd358f80-b1b0-11e8-9385-2fd6f73c98a7.png)
Same here

Sorry for the probelm. Please post your addresses - I can play manual faucet again. 
Unfortunately there was a problem with rinkeby - some details here: https://blog.infura.io/rinkeby-consensus-post-mortem-4abbcace0539
Unfortunately the faucet did not yet recover from the problem and @karalabe who knows how to solve it is in holiday/transit. When he is back we will increase this bus-factor of 1 to >=2
Also I hope one outcome of ETHBerlin will be that we get a second/backup faucet - see: https://github.com/ethberlin-hackathon/ETHBerlin-Teambuilding/issues/8
Sorry again and please post your addresses and how much rinkeby eth you need and I will give you some from my stash.
I figured it had something to do with the recent problems. Thanks for the offer but I have plenty of rinkeby eth for now. Just thought I would bring this issue up with the devs
